President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8pm on Wednesday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -  President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation at 8pm on Wednesday. Ramaphosa is expected to provide an update on the government's strategies to manage the coronavirus pandemic. READ: 106 new COVID-19 deaths recorded Earlier this week, in his weekly newsletter, the president urged South Africans to continue adhering to health regulations in order to avoid a second wave of infections.